      "content": "That's a good start, but the execs are going to push harder than that. They aren't just going to talk about \"fairness\" in the abstract; they're going to get into the weeds about actual performance. They might argue that focusing on diversity actually lowers the standard of excellence for the company. Can you expand on that? Specifically, how would they argue that prioritizing race over \"objective\" metrics leads to a decline in competitive edge or competence within a workforce?",
